THE HAWKS have arrested a 25-year-old man and seized drugs
valued at more than R8.9 million in Somerset West. The Hawks’ Narcotics Enforcement Bureau (SANEB) and Crime
Intelligence officers received a tip that narcotics were secretly being kept
inside a storeroom. “The team found heroin, tik and mandrax including a
handgun.  A vehicle reportedly belonging
to the apprehended suspect was also seized,” Police spokesperson Captain Philani
Nkwalase said. The Hawks National Head, Lieutenant General Godfrey Lebeya
has congratulated the arrest. He said the discovery by the multidisciplinary team saying
that this demonstrated the police commitment to reducing the availability of
drugs in and around Cape Town. The suspect is expected to appear at the Somerset West
Magistrate’s Court soon. 